item.title: 【Albums (lossy)】Dolby Atmos - Steven Wilson - The Harmony Codex [Dolby Atmos E-AC3-JOC | 16-bit/48kHz | 5.1 | 768 kb/s]
item.description:
Genre: Electronic, Rock, Pop
Style: Prog Rock, Art Rock
Year: 2023
Source: Blu-ray

"The Harmony Codex" is the seventh studio album by British musician and record producer Steven Wilson, released on 29 September 2023 through Virgin Music Group. The album was first announced on 29 August 2023 with the release of lead single "Economies of Scale". Since then, the tracks "Impossible Tightrope", "Rock Bottom", and "What Life Brings" have been released as singles. Along with the release of the standalone record, it is also released was a three-disc limited edition box set featuring a collection of bonus tracks under the name Harmonic Distortion.

The album is said to be "a genre-spanning collection that opens up like a musical puzzle box" and musically more complex than Wilson's previous album. Steven Wilson supposedly worked on the album "in a studio tucked inside a garage of a North London townhouse", piecing together the tracks with remote help from collaborators Ninet Tayeb, Craig Blundell, Adam Holzman, Jack Dangers, and Sam Fogarino.

Steven Wilson about the album: "My seventh album The Harmony Codex is a real trip, a beautiful and experimental 65 minute labyrinth of a record, with almost every one of its 10 tracks taking a different musical approach. I really hope you will all get to hear the album as intended - a continuous musical journey, or a piece of 'cinema for the ears'. I couldn’t be prouder of this album and I think you are going to enjoy it too!"
